CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published n the Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, April 6, 1957, pg. A8 reads: "Outstanding All-City Musicians - Among the outstanding musicians of Pittsburgh's high schools were Helen Stroud, voila player, of Westinghouse; Donna DeGasperi and Claudia Conrad, cellists of South Hills, and Elizabeth (Betsy) Johnson, flutist, of Westinghouse, who played in all-city high school orchestra at its concert Monday evening in Oakland's Carnegie Music Hall. Harris Photo.
TitMainTitle: Helen Stroud, Donna DeGasperi, Claudia Conrad, and Elizabeth "Betsy" Johnson, standing beside stairway in Carnegie Music Hall for All-City high school orchestra concert
